  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Safety Officer (WSHO)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1.Discharge duties as relevant in the WSH Act, WSH (Workplace Safety and Health (Officers) Regulations and Environmental Public Health Act</p><p>2. Implement and maintain WSH Management system.</p><p>3. Assist the WSH committee chairman, act as secretary to the committee and provide advice to the WSH Committee members in relevant to WSH matters.</p><p>4. Conduct team/ individual WSHE inspections and produce relevant reports and follow-ups and statistics</p><p>5. Organize / conduct WSHE briefing/ training /WSH Campaign to all employees.</p><p>6. Develop and maintain the Risk Management system of the project.</p><p>7. To investigate any incidents/accidents and advise on the remedial measures to be taken into prevent any recurrence.</p><p>8. To recommend to the occupier of the workplace or other in charge of the workplace reasonably practicable measures.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>At least 10 years LTA/MRT WSHO working experience in construction industry</p><p>Familiar with OHSAS 18001 and ISO 14001 and GGBS preferred</p><p>MOM Registered WSH Officer, NEA Environmental Control Officer.</p><p>Good communication skills to liaise with associates, clients, government authorities.</p><p>Good team player.</p>",
